# Components Rule

- Use functional components only.
- Keep props typed (`type` or `interface` in TypeScript).
- Export component from local `index.ts` barrel.
- Keep imports ordered: external libs -> internal aliases -> relative imports.
- Prefer Tailwind utility classes for spacing/layout (`p-*`, `m-*`, `gap-*`, `grid`, `flex`).
- Use consistent spacing scale (4/8/12/16/24).
- Keep UI components presentational; move stateful logic to hooks.
- If using JavaScript, define `propTypes` and sensible `defaultProps`.
- Add minimal accessibility defaults (`aria-*`, labels, semantic tags).
- Avoid inline styles unless dynamic style cannot be expressed with utilities.
